<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>About | James Andersen Attorney</title>
    <style>
      :root {
        --gold: #d6b24c; /* pulled from the "Subscribe Now" button */
        --navy: #1e1e3f;
        --light-gray: #f4f4f4;
      }

      body {
        margin: 0;
        font-family: "Segoe UI", Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
        background-color: var(--light-gray);
        color: var(--navy);
      }

      .layout-wrapper {
        display: flex;
        min-height: 100vh;
      }

      .sidebar {
        flex: 1;
        background-color: var(--gold);
      }

      .content {
        flex: 4;
        background-color: var(--light-gray);
        padding: 60px 40px;
        max-width: 1000px;
        margin: auto;
      }

      .content h1 {
        font-size: 36px;
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 40px;
      }

      .content h2 {
        font-size: 24px;
        margin-top: 30px;
        color: var(--navy);
      }

      .content p {
        font-size: 18px;
        line-height: 1.7;
        color: #333;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
      }

      footer {
        background-color: var(--navy);
        color: white;
        text-align: center;
        padding: 20px;
        font-size: 14px;
      }

      footer p {
        margin: 5px 0;
      }

      @media (max-width: 900px) {
        .layout-wrapper {
          flex-direction: column;
        }

        .sidebar {
          display: none;
        }

        .content {
          padding: 40px 20px;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="layout-wrapper">
      <div class="sidebar"></div>

      <div class="content">
        <h1>About James Andersen</h1>

        <h2>Decades of Experience</h2>
        <p>
          James Andersen has practiced law for over 47 years, bringing
          unparalleled depth and dedication to every client interaction.
          Licensed in 1977 after graduating from South Texas College of Law, he
          began his career with a clear sense of purpose: to advocate for
          individuals and families facing complex legal issues with clarity,
          empathy, and skill.
        </p>
        <p>
          His experience spans a wide range of legal areas, but his core focus
          has long been in foreclosure defense, probate, and real estate law.
          Whether representing homeowners fighting to keep their properties or
          families navigating sensitive estate matters, James is known for being
          both strategic and compassionate.
        </p>
        <p>
          Prior to entering the legal profession, James served his country in
          the Vietnam War, an experience that sharpened his discipline and
          resilience. He later worked in the political sector, where he learned
          how to navigate systems, advocate persuasively, and communicate
          effectively under pressure. These qualities continue to define his
          legal practice today.
        </p>
        <p>
          Throughout his career, James has maintained a hands-on, client-first
          approach. He is deeply committed to building relationships based on
          trust and ensuring that every legal document, filing, and negotiation
          is handled with precision and care. Clients appreciate his ability to
          translate legal language into plain terms and his unwavering
          commitment to protecting their interests.
        </p>
        <p>
          James's reputation has been built almost entirely through
          word-of-mouth referrals — a reflection of the lasting impact he has
          had on those he serves. He believes in doing the hard work behind the
          scenes so that his clients can focus on what matters most: finding
          clarity, resolution, and peace of mind.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="sidebar"></div>
    </div>

    <footer>
      <p>📧 jandersen.law@gmail.com | 📞 (281) 488-2800</p>
      <p>© 2025 James Andersen, Attorney at Law. All rights reserved.</p>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
